{
  "global": "Determine U(T,P) for a Curie-law dielectric by combining the Curie susceptibility with thermodynamic Maxwell relations to show that internal energy is independent of polarization at constant temperature.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Establish electric field as a function of polarization and temperature using Curie law",
      "atomics": [
        "Express susceptibility χ in terms of polarizability and number density: χ = nα",
        "Apply Curie law α = K/T to obtain χ(T) = nK/T",
        "Use P = χ(T)ε₀E to derive E = PT/(nKε₀)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Apply thermodynamic Maxwell relations to relate entropy and field",
      "atomics": [
        "Identify Helmholtz free energy F = U - TS with differential dF = -SdT + Edp",
        "Derive the Maxwell relation (∂S/∂p)_T = -(∂E/∂T)_p from equality of mixed partials",
        "Calculate (∂E/∂T)_p = P/(nKε₀) using E = PT/(nKε₀) with p held constant",
        "Conclude (∂S/∂p)_T = -P/(nKε₀)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Evaluate the internal energy derivative with respect to dipole moment at constant temperature",
      "atomics": [
        "Apply the first law dU = TdS + Edp to write (∂U/∂p)_T = T(∂S/∂p)_T + E",
        "Substitute (∂S/∂p)_T = -P/(nKε₀) and E = PT/(nKε₀)",
        "Calculate the sum: T(-P/(nKε₀)) + PT/(nKε₀) = 0",
        "Conclude (∂U/∂p)_T = 0"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Convert the dipole moment derivative to polarization derivative",
      "atomics": [
        "Use p = PV where V is constant volume",
        "Transform (∂U/∂p)_T = 0 to (∂U/∂P)_T = V⁻¹(∂U/∂p)_T = 0"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Integrate to determine the functional form of U(T,P)",
      "atomics": [
        "From (∂U/∂P)_T = 0, recognize that U is independent of P at each temperature T",
        "Express this as U(T,P) = h(T) where h is a function of T alone",
        "Match to the given form U(T,P) = CT + f(P) to conclude f(P) = constant",
        "Set the constant to zero by reference state choice to obtain U(T,P) = CT"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Verify dimensional consistency: [C][T] = (energy/temperature) × (temperature) = energy",
    "Confirm physical interpretation: the entropy decrease from polarization exactly balances the work done by the field, leaving internal energy independent of polarization state"
  ],
  "gold_actions": {
    "global": "Solve for U(T,P) by integrating the thermodynamic constraint (∂U/∂P)_T = 0 derived from Curie law and Maxwell relations",
    "subtasks": [
      {
        "subtask": "Compute E(T,P) from Curie law susceptibility",
        "atomics": [
          "Calculate χ(T) = nα = n(K/T) = nK/T",
          "Solve P = χ(T)ε₀E for E to get E(T,P) = PT/(nKε₀)",
          "Verify ∂E/∂T|_P = P/(nKε₀) > 0"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Apply Maxwell relation from Helmholtz free energy",
        "atomics": [
          "Establish dF = -SdT + Edp from F = U - TS",
          "Derive (∂S/∂p)_T = -(∂E/∂T)_p using ∂²F/∂p∂T = ∂²F/∂T∂p",
          "Substitute ∂E/∂T|_p = P/(nKε₀) to get (∂S/∂p)_T = -P/(nKε₀)",
          "Interpret as entropy decreasing when dipole moment increases at constant T"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Show that (∂U/∂p)_T = 0 using the first law",
        "atomics": [
          "Write (∂U/∂p)_T = T(∂S/∂p)_T + E from dU = TdS + Edp",
          "Substitute (∂S/∂p)_T = -P/(nKε₀) to get T(-P/(nKε₀)) = -TP/(nKε₀)",
          "Substitute E = PT/(nKε₀) to add TP/(nKε₀)",
          "Conclude -TP/(nKε₀) + TP/(nKε₀) = 0"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Convert to polarization dependence and integrate",
        "atomics": [
          "Use p = PV with constant V to get (∂U/∂P)_T = 0",
          "Integrate ∂U/∂P = 0 at fixed T to find U(P,T) = g(T)",
          "Match the ansatz U = CT + f(P) to conclude f(P) = 0"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Write the final answer",
        "atomics": [
          "State U(T,P) = CT as the unique solution consistent with Curie law",
          "Note that internal energy depends only on temperature, not on polarization state achieved",
          "Verify this form satisfies both the given structure U = CT + f(P) and the derived constraint (∂U/∂P)_T = 0"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "global_atomics": [
      "Check [U] = [C][T] with [C] = energy/temperature yields [energy]",
      "Verify that the entropy cost T(∂S/∂P)_T = -TP/(nKε₀) exactly cancels the field work E·V = (PT/(nKε₀))·V at constant T and V"
    ]
  }
}
```

FINAL ANSWER: U(T, P) = CT
